"Modern Theatre" explores the main strategies of acting and directing in the 20th and 21st centuries. The aim of the subject is to create a historical-theoretical context for practical theatre techniques.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the main strategies of acting and directing in the 20th and 21st centuries and to interpret them as application potential. To explore some strategies for acting or directing in more detail.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - Orients oneself in the main strategies of acting and directing in the 20th and 21st centuries and understands them as application potential. - Has explored some of the strategies of acting or directing in more detail.
